summary: In this context, 1,4-dichlorobenzene and 4-xylene are both mentioned as volatile organic compounds (VOCs) analyzed in post-MF (microfiltration) water samples during a study on wastewater treatment processes. However, there is no direct discussion of their relationship, interactions, or comparative significance in the context of the treatment process or environmental impact, indicating they are simply part of a broader list of analytes monitored.
